animal.description:
Huey & Lewie are spending time in a foster home. Here's what their foster has to say about them:

"They're doing great! We really love them! I personally would hate to see them separated because I do think they're bonded and are so used to being around each other. Their personalities complement each other perfectly as well. 

Lewie is the more outgoing one, he's like a goofy Scooby-Doo, always marching around looking for something to get his nose in. He loves climbing up on chairs and on our outdoor table to curl up and take a nap. He's very cuddly and social and always wants to be near people. He gets excited by everything but is slightly aloof in an adorable way, in that he will run around and do his own thing but then come over for attention. He's house trained and has done well with every other dogs he's encountered. He likes running around our property and hanging out with Huey. 

Huey is a little more timid at first, but he's opened up a lot since he got here. He's always shaking his little nub tail at a 1000 miles a second. He loves to body up to you for pets and love, and really never had an undesirable behavior. He walks perfectly on the leash and doesn't leave your side. He gets along well with our other dogs and loves to eat. He hasn't quite become as brazen as Lewie in climbing up on furniture, but he's become super calm and comfy at home compared to how terrified he was in the shelter when I got him. I remember he just hid in the corner when I met him; now he's a greeter and a happy boy. Lewie is his therapy dog."

Huey was part of a playgroup with other dogs on 10/2/20. Huey was unsure about new dogs and appeared to be conflict and possibly prey driven.

animal.description:
Gina went on a foster field trip. Here is what her field trip buddy had to say about her: "I had the esteemed privilege of taking Gina out on a foster field trip. When she came out of the kennels she was SO incredibly excited that she was practically pulling me out the door. She was a pro at getting into the car. However, once inside she just couldn't contain her excitement. All she wanted to do was snuggle and roll around the car as I drove. For this reason, we decided to walk locally in the nearby neighborhood. Gina is super high energy and does pull the leash. However, whenever I stopped to tell her "no, she would kindly oblige (at least for a little bit) but only after giving me a few licks. We stopped a few times for a break, during which Gina would pretend to be a lap dog, roll around in the grass, give licks, and ask for pets. It seems she knows sit, and perhaps even paw/shake. Overall, she did very well on our walk. She mostly ignored other dogs and people walking by. But sometimes, she was in the mood to try to chase cars as they passed us. Gina is a hyper and happy-go-lucky girl. She is looking for an adult-only home where she would be the only pet. She would do best with adopters who are patient and willing to spend time on training, but who also want to include her in their active and high-energy lifestyle so she can tire herself out after a long day."

Gina was part of a playgroup with other dogs on 12/6. She kept to herself at first, but was friendly when approached. She became more friendly and social with time, and was a greeter when new dogs entered the yard.

Gina was part of a playgroup with other dogs on 12/10/20. Gina was friendly, social, and patient. Her play style varied depending on who she was interacting with. 

Gina was part of a playgroup with other dogs on 1/16/21. Gina was social, playful at times, and offered appropriate corrections. 

Gina was part of play group on 1/17. She was friendly, social, and playful. She was also very tolerant and offered appropriate corrections when necessary.

Gina was part of play group on 1/18. She was friendly, social, and playful.

Gina was part of a playgroup with other dogs on 1/21/20. Gina was very sweet and social.

1/31 update:  Please note, we are looking for adopters who currently have outgoing, socialized dogs for this pup and two of his siblings.  Because they are so fearful, they will need another dog to show them the way and help them come out of their shells.  Adopters will need to have lots of patience and give them plenty of time to adapt.

Sterling Archer is a 14-week old Labrador/Hound mix pup who was rescued in VA from a farm with many other dogs. He has been in foster now and is developing good house manners and has made good progress with potty training but will need a continued routine. 

When full-grown, he will be a large dog. He would do best in a home who will provide positive reinforcement puppy training. We don't know how he will do with cats.

animal.description:
Do you need a little more joy and faith in your life? Here they are! Joy Be and Faith Be are a bonded pair of 14 year old rat terriers.They came to Angels after their owner became terminally ill. They are now ready to find a home where they can enjoy their senior years in style. They must be adopted together.

Joy, who weighs 16 pounds, would love to have a fenced in backyard where she can run and explore. She loves to sit next to you on a soft couch and be surrounded in blankets.

Faith, who weighs 24 pounds, is the more laid back of the two. She is a big cuddle bug. Faith likes to groom Joy, and is happy to be around other dogs her size and energy.

Their foster mom says that it was clear both dogs were housebroken in their prior home and are doing well learning a new routine. They do need frequent trips outside to minimize accidents.

Both dogs have lost most of their hearing over time, and can get anxious when they are in new surroundings. They also tend to communicate with a very loud bark.

Joy Be and Faith Be would do best with adopters who are home most of the time, have a quiet household with minimal activity, and who have a fenced in backyard.

For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org

An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online. http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms

Please be sure to like our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/angelsrescue.

animal.description:
Bensin is a 2 year old, Hound/Husky mix, who was found as a stray and rescued from a shelter. He is young, energetic, loving and docile. Bensin will race around the yard as easily as he'll nap quietly in the house. He can be a tad stubborn and vocal (that's the hound in him), but a correction always works, especially if a treat is involved. He sits like a pro and takes treats very gently. And he's got the head-tilt down-a very curious, observant, intelligent dog who will give you lots of ear kisses.

Bensin is a big boy-lanky. He's underweight, and when he gets to his ideal, I imagine he'll be closer to 65 pounds. Bensin is also very beautiful. His fur is so soft, you'll want to live in it!

He has shown no signs of aggression regarding food or toys. He greets other dogs beautifully. He wants to play with my cats, but when they sit still for him, he is calm and careful.

Bensin would like a family who's home a lot and has a yard where he can play and run, and he'd love regular walks. An outdoorsy hiking family would make him a very happy boy. But it's not necessary. Some daily physical and mental stimulation and being part of his very own home with his very own people is all he needs to be on Cloud 9.

For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org

An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online. http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms

This 1-2 year old girl has got to be the SWEETEST thing ever! She was found as a stray in morning traffic on a four lane road, looking for food. Even then, she was the happiest dog.

Sweet Cheeks has done well with any other dogs and all people she has came in contact with. That being said, she does still have some puppy left in her, so if you're excited, SO IS SHE! Once she knows you, she calms down a lot and is happy just walking beside you on a leash. 

Sweet Cheeks is PHENOMENAL in a home! This pretty girl also does well in a crate, but once she is left in there for a while, she begins to get restless and starts to whine for you.

Sweet Cheeks could adapt well to really any home, but we would recommend any children in the home be 5+ due to her size.

Bitsha is a lovely Pitt Bull Mix dog about 1 year old. She is supper energetic she needs someone that is going to taker her on adventures and long walks. We are a Southern California based rescue and do nothing adopt further than an hour from our headquarters in Inglewood, Ca. we do not adopt out more than a 30 minute radius. We appreciate you being understanding and Patient as we attempt to go back to a new normal.

animal.description:
I never expected to be at the shelter for so long! I really am a good girl, super smart and trainable, just maybe a tiny bit finicky. Super smart might be an understatement, actually. I know tricks like how to sit AND how to "sit pretty" where I get up on my tippy toes and look adorable. I also showed the shelter staff not to underestimate me when I came in on the week of July 4th - when fireworks went off, I broke through every door that wasn't deadbolted and found my way outside! Luckily, I knew to hang around the building and stuck to the woods until they caught me the next day, but that was the first time a dog opened six different doors to get out on their own. I sure showed them!

I am a very determined girl who knows her mind, as you can tell, and that's part of what makes me so fun. I love humans including kids, but I don't tolerate naughtiness of any degree and will put an overenthusiastic child in their place. So I would be best with older kids or a family that understands that a dog needs boundaries and that I have my own rights to protect my space.

I am pretty sure cats are evil creatures from another world, so I do NOT want to be in a house with them. I tend to be reactive to most dogs as well, so a home with no other pets is best.

This is probably the point I should admit I have some terrible separation anxiety. I really do not like the idea of being on my own, and I've already admitted I know how to open doors so it's not really an option to leave me alone for long. I also am likely to pick a favorite person out of a group and be very protective of them, because that's what friends do is keep each other safe. I don't always understand that humans like to roughhouse with each other, though, so if I see someone getting rough with one of my favorite humans, I might think you're threatening them and try to scare you away with some intense barking.

All in all, I may sound picky but I'm an incredibly nice girl who loves challenging her brain. Whether it's coming up with new tricks, exploring with my favorite people, or running around with the zoomies, I love when I can try new things and feel safe at the same time. I really want a family and will do everything I can to keep them safe.

*Marquis (pronounced "Markie") cannot be in a home with young kids (below age 12), cats, other dogs, or other small animals (birds, rats, reptiles, bunnies, etc.) for the safety of Marquis and other animals.

animal.description:
Hiya! My name is Boltz and no I am not faster than the speed of lighting but my energy is electric and I will light up your life with joy, for sure! Don't get me wrong, I can be fast and would love to be a part of your outdoor adventures but am perfectly happy with some lazy tv days too! I love to lounge around and spend time with hoomans of all sizes....and dogs too! I like to be where the people are-- even if I'm in my crate. I find it very comforting when I can see what's going on. My foster momma says that I am a very sweet and well behaved boy. I try my best to make my hoomans happy. I love yummy treats and listen especially well for a handful of themz. As much as I love my foster family, I am ready for a home of my own. Are you my home?

To bring Boltz home, please apply here-
https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/19764/generic or email cynthia@threelittlepittiesrescue.org if you have an application on file.

The adoption fee is $500 and includes all vaccines (DHPP & booster, Bordatella, Rabies), spay/neuter, microchip, multiple dewormings, flea preventative, heartworm preventative injection that covers 6 months after adoption, a high quality nylon Martingale collar, a 30 day trial of pet insurance, transport from TX to the PNW, and many years of priceless memories.

**APPLICATION REQUIRED FOR A RESPONSE**

IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING THIS PET, PLEASE COMPLETE AN ADOPTION APPLICATION FOUND ON OUR WEBSITE HTTP://FUREVERTAILS.COM/ADOPTIONS. We process applications ONLY - there is no guarantee that you will get a response to an inquiry.

MEET MOBY:

Moby is a sweet, energetic Australian Cattle Dog mix. His date of birth is 11/25/20. Moby and his three sibbling were surrendered to a high intake shelter along with their Autralian Cattle Dog momma, Mollie. Puppies need homes where someone is home more often than not for proper house training and socialization. Moby will still need leash training and crate training. He will do best with children over 6 years old, since his breed is classified as herding dogs. Moby will not be a good fit for an apartment/condo lifestyle or mobile home community as this is a working class breed dog and will be very active. He has been exposed to other dogs and children. Moby is at the age where socialization is very important as they are just beginning to show their personalities and they are curious about the world around them. Please keep in mind that puppies are challenging and they are a big responsibility as they are prone to chewing, they will have accidents in the house and they will cause you sleepless nights while crate training. Moby will need a lot of mental stimulus and physical activity to help him stay happy and healthy. Moby is seeking an active family that will love her furever! 

Moby is: 
Current on age appropriate vaccines
Dewormed
Heartworm Tested: Negative
Recieving Heartworm prevention and Flea/tick prevention
Microchipped
Neutered

ADOPTION FEE: $350.00

FUREVER TAILS IS A NON-PROFIT, NO-KILL, FOSTER HOME BASED ANIMAL RESCUE BASED OUT OF OAKLAND TOWNSHIP, MI. animal.description:
Meet Mailman! This sweet Lab mix is ready for home on 2/2 from Woburn MA. This sweet boy is a tripod as he had a rear leg recently amputated. He was spotted by a woman that runs a rural mail route again and again. He was obviously injured and was losing weight (abandoned in a very rural area of MS). Once rescued, x-rays showed that his back leg had been broken in two places and healed back incorrectly which resulted in pain and required amputation. Like many tripods, he is getting through his new life on 3 legs just fine! He is best without a lot of stairs and like many 3-legged pups, does best with carpet or runners / rugs as wood or tile floors can be slippery. He is very human and dog friendly!

Read through our adoption process and other adoption FAQs here www.rescueinc.dog/FAQs

All of our pups come with the following: 


	Spayed or Neutered
	Age appropriate vaccinations + dewormed + 4DX test (if older than 6 months)
	New martingale collar with 6' lead + temp ID tag
	30 days free insurance to be activated within 24 hours of your wellness visit with your veterinarian
	Microchip with free registration for your new pup, but also for any other pets in your household too!
	Southern pups, younger than 6 months, come with 1 month of flea / tick / heartworm prevention to prevent any lapse of protection 
	Our southern dogs, 6 months and older, come with a **Proheart 6 injection which provides 6 months of Heartworm protection (approx value of $100) + dose of flea / tick preventative


**dogs surrendered to us in MA do not recieve the Proheart 6 injection but do go home with 1 month of flea / tick / heartworm preventative so there is no lapse in protection

Ages listed can be approximate and breed mixes are a best guess based on physical characteristics. 

If you are seeing this listing on Petfinder, please apply through the link on our website at www.rescueinc.dog/adopt 

Please do not email with questions or message through Petfinder. Communication with the rescue always starts with submitting an application. 

If you see this listing, the pup is still available. We pull listings after 2 to 3 viable applications are submitted.

animal.description:
Pinkerton and Weezer are the newest "Not" weilers to join R.E.A.L. Rott Rescue. Both boys are sweet, sassy, and playful. They will be adopted to separate homes, not together. We also have a female littermate named Rivers. She is also available. The pups love other dogs and will be fine with children who have been brought up to be respectful with animals. Our foster homes work on house breaking, crate training and basic obedience.

Adoption Requirements: No Exceptions
- Cannot reside in an area with BSL
- No apartments/rentals


These pups are currently available for adoption through R.E.A.L. Rott Rescue. Adoption fee includes DHPP and rabies, vaccines; deworming; microchip and registration; heartworm test (if over 6 months old) and HW preventative to last thru adoption trial; and spay/neuter. 

***PLEASE READ THIS ENTIRE POST & FOLLOW THE INSTRUCTIONS****

Please note that our organization is entirely foster based and we are all volunteers. We are based in the greater Cleveland area (OH) however we do have fosters in Ohio, Pennsylvania, Maryland and Michigan. Once you submit your application, it may take up to 21 business days for us to get back to you. Please be patient.


R.E.A.L. Rott Rescue is 100% foster based; we are not a shelter & each animal is in an actual home with a foster family. We receive an overwhelming amount of emails and applications so please be patient. To qualify, an application MUST BE filled out, a Vet Check MUST BE completed by our team, and an approval (or denial) email will be sent. This is all prior to scheduling any "meet and greet".

Vet Checks:
When adopting through our rescue, we 'ALWAYS' do a vet check on each applicant's pets that they have owned over the past 5 years. Please make sure to call your vet to grant them permission to release this information to our rescue when we call. That being said, all of the animals in each applicant's home must be UTD on all of their vaccines (DHLPP & Rabies), on monthly HW preventative, and spayed/neutered. Please make sure that the veterinarian listed on your application has seen your pet and can confirm the vetting is current.

Notes When Applying:
If you're interested in adopting one of our available dogs:
1. Apply at www.realrottweilerrescue.com.
2. Please specify if you would like us to screen for other dogs if the dog you are interested in is no longer available.
3. Please be sure to call your vet to grant our organization permission to do a vet check on your current and past pet/s.
4. Please be honest & truthful on your application. We always do a vet check!
5. We do adopt outside of the state of Ohio however, you must have an approved application, you and any humans and canines residing in the home must all make the trip to our foster home/s when meeting a prospective rescue dog. (We do not transport)

animal.description:
Kitten is a hound mix looking for a home of her own. She is very friendly, loves people!
The Adoption Process


	If you are ready to meet the pet, please fill out an online adoption application by copying and pasting the following link into your internet browser: https://www.petstablished.com/adoption_form/10666/generic
	Once your application is submitted, we will contact the vet reference provided. If you do not yet have a vet, please provide three personal references these could be family and friends who can attest to your pet parenting skills.
	A volunteer will schedule a phone interview with you. The interview and application help our fosters find their forever home by ensuring a good match. 
	The Louisa Humane Society does not have a brick and mortar facility, so all of our pets are in foster care. Once approved, the foster parent will reach out to arrange a visit. The foster family can tell you all about her likes, dislikes, and little quirks. 
	The application and visit do not oblige you to adopt, but if youre ready to take the pet home as your furry forever friend, the adoption fee is $150.


Should the match turn out less than perfect, or if you are unwilling or unable to care for an adopted animal, the Louisa Humane Society will take the animal back into our care.

animal.description:
*Due to concerns surrounding COVID-19, we have reformatted the way that we do adoptions in order to follow social distancing protocols. We are thrilled that so many people want to adopt right now, but we are not equipped to handle the large number of calls, applications, and email inquiries we are receiving. We are no longer answering phone calls and are doing all communications with adopters via email. If you have a dog you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application before sending us emails. When your application has been processed, you will receive an email from us with further instructions on how to adopt. You do not need a new application for every dog that you are interested in adopting. 

At MAMCO we understand that in order to continue rescuing moms and babies, we must stretch our finances as far as we are able. For this reason we use variable adoption pricing. By assigning higher adoption fees to high demand moms and puppies, we are able to rescue more families in need.The money raised through these adoptions acts as a benefactor to moms and puppies in our care who require expensive veterinary treatments, have behavioral issues, or need more time to find a home. We often reduce the adoption fees on these harder-to-place moms and puppies to help them find forever families. Adoption fees vary, but all include spay or neuter, microchip, up to date vaccinations and deworming, rabies vaccine at the time of spay or neuter, and 30 days of pet insurance. We also cover hernia repair and cherry eye repair at the time of spay or neuter. Applications can be filled out at mamcorescue.org.

animal.description:
Waif was found living on a construction site with another dog. It was obvious they were both in rough shape and needed help immediately. Waif had a noticeable limp and hairloss throughout her body...but given the conditions she was found in, we're thankful that's all that seemed to be wrong. These pups were sleeping in an active construction zone; screws, broken glass, and staples littered the same floor that they slept on and machines were constantly coming in and out of the site. It's a miracle she wasn't in worse condition.

After being rescued from the construction zone, Waif was still very scared. She had to live in fear on the construction site to survive and was struggling to learn to relax. She has made progress in a foster home and is much more accepting of people than she used to be. Waif really seems to come out of her shell around other dogs! She has been in foster for months and is doing FANTASTIC! Waif looks forward to her daily walks with foster siblings and is a super star on a leash! 

Waif was seen by a vet and had an x-ray done. She's been on pain medication, but there hasn't been much improvement in her limp. Thanks to our generous donors, 4 Paws 4 Life Rescue will be preforming the TPLO surgery at our veterinarian to stabilize the affected leg before she goes to her forever family.

Here is a link to a video of Waif being reunited with the other dogs found at the construction site: https://youtu.be/g5C1Lj7kq74

Here is a link to a video of Waif being temperament tested off leash: https://youtu.be/8NpFbowNmAc

This is all the information we have currently.


	Approved Applicants may make the adoption fee payment by clicking donate above. Partial adoption fees will not hold a dog.
	Dogs adopted with our rescue come with FREE training from #GoodPup to help you build strong bonds from the start!
	If upon meeting the dog of your choosing at an adoption event you find that you aren't a good match, your deposit will be refunded minus a 10% administration fee.
	Adoption fees include vaccines up until time of adoption, microchip, spay/neuter and 1st 30 days of free Pet insurance. We are not affiliated with Pet First pet insurance. (you have to sign up for the insurance or it will not go into effect). 
	Adopters can go to our vet for medical issues that may arise in 1st 3 days of adoption. 
	The dogs in our care are fostered in Colorado, Texas, and New Mexico. While all dogs are picked up during our scheduled times, sometimes transport dates change due to unforeseen circumstances.

animal.description:
Wyn

 

Located in Sidney NE

3.5 years old

Shar Pei/Terrier/Muppet fusion 

LOVES other dogs and will do best in a home with at least 1 other playful dog 

Cats unknown, chases cats outside but has never met a cat inside

Fantastic with older children, way too hyper for young kids

House trained

Crate trained and knows some commands when she is willing to listen haha

Must have a secure fenced in yard 

Loves to pull her "boy" on his skateboard

Amazing running partner 

Fully vetted

35lbs

 

Wyn came into our rescue as a bitty puppy with her siblings and momma. Wyn was the last of her litter to be adopted as she was quite

The spirited little scruffy. Her fosfef family fell in love with her and she has been there for the past 3 years. She has an amazing bond with the human children of the family specifically a boy high schooler. Unfortunately this family is going through a painful unheivel by way of a divorce and is being forced to move into an appt. They cannot take more than 2 dogs to the appt and they have more than that. They found a family to temp take 1 but their other dogs are older and have less energy. No one will take Wyn. Wyn is a FORCE in the best way! She is a free spirit, a wild child, she lives every moment of her life to the fullest with unbridled passion. We is about to lose everything she knows, she is about to lose her best friend, her family, her home. Her mom, human siblings and all of us at HPPAW are devastated. The mom has tried everything in her power to figure something else out, but we haven't been able to and now we have no choice but to list her for adoption with the hope that the 2 families can stay in touch. 

 

No unkind words, this is a truly life altering decision that hasn't been decided lightly and those parties named above are very emotional about the situation.

 $200.00 Adoption Fee 

(Which is considered a non refundable donation and being we are a 501c3 organization it is tax deductible. The fee itself is not negotiable, our vets don't negotiate and thus neither do we.)

To Contact Us

Message us through our website http://www.highplainspaw.org

Message the Facebook Page at https://www.facebook.com/HighPlainsPAW

Fill out our Adoption Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/adoption-application

Fill out our Foster Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/foster-application

Email us at highplainspaw@gmail.com

Call our VOICEMAIL at (402)957-1578

 

WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY ALL OUR DOGS ARE LOCATED IN FOSTER HOMES. This means there is no place for you to go in person to view our dogs. We ask that an application be filled out and we will go from there!

 He does have a thyroid issue, which explains the thinning fur on his lower back. But the good news is it's easy and inexpensive to treat. Medication is only $15 a month. Please share Bear! PLEASE CONSIDER ADOPTING OUR SWEET BEAR. HE'S LIVED THE SHELTER LIFE LONG ENOUGH AND DESERVES A SAFE HOME

animal.description: Meet Buster. This super sweet guy was returned to us after almost 4 years because of his owners failing health. Buster was very well taken care of and is very sweet and mellow pup. Although, he is used to a quieter home and quieter neighborhood and will bark at noises and people he doesn't know. Buster does get frightened with loud noises. He is housebroken, up to date with vaccines, microchipped and kept on monthly heartworm prevention. He has had some allergy issues since he was returned and we currently have him on Apoquel for his itching. He may need to stay on this as he is doing well, but we are not certain if some of the scratching is due to him being a little stressed from losing his human best friend. Buster loves to play with other dogs, but may do best with a buddy more his size. Buster would prefer a home with a fenced in yard as this is what he is used to, as well as having an owner that is home often or another friendly dog in the home to keep him company so he isn't alone. He is currently about 4 years old and about 65 pounds. Buster's adoption fee is $250.00. He will be sent with a months worth of Apoquel if he needs to stay on that. If you are interested in adopting Buster, please visit our website www.LHARinc.org go to Adopt and complete the dog adoption application.

animal.description:
Hi! I'm Tucker, yup ,yup, yup! that is me in the picture, Tucker the Amazing Begahoula. That's short for Beagle/Catahoula leopard dog. Begahoula fits me better, because just like my name I am one of a kind! I am two years old and 45 pounds of pure puppy exuberance! I am super duper smart and I love to play games, Frisbee is my favorite but I will play with sniff, tug, chase, I try fetch sometimes, but I laugh when my foster mom has to chase me so I do not always give the ball back. WoooWooo (dog laughing sounds) , sorry but it is just so much fun to run. Then, when we are done playing my next favorite thing to do is cuddle, oh I love a good cuddle, snuggle, pet my belly kind of break. I sooooo do enjoy laying on my back on the couch with all four paws in the air just getting a good old belly rub, nothin better if you ask this pup. I love other dogs, I mean who wouldn't all us dogs are awesome. Now I know your saying this pup is too good to be true, so I will tell you what things I still need a little help with. I can get really excited and run so fast that I can knock things over. I don't chew anything but I am curious and will investigate your personal items. Things like shoes and little people toys. I just like to gather them up and keep them next to me, cuz it reminds me of you when you are not with me. So I'm lookin for an awesome family, I've got lost of love to give and can't wait to meet you.

Tucker's adoption fee is $250 which includes his neuter, vaccinations (rabies, distemper, lepto), microchip, heartworm test and flea and heartworm prevention. Also, six weeks of obedience classes if you chose to do so.

DUE TO COVID-19 RESTRICTIONS: TO HELP US LIMIT THE NUMBER OF PEOPLE IN THE BUILDING, OUR ADOPTION CENTER IS OPEN BY APPOINTMENT ONLY TO APPROVED APPLICANTS. PLEASE FILL OUT THE ADOPTION APPLICATION IF YOU WOULD LIKE TO MEET TUCKER. FILLING OUT AN APPLICATION DOES NOT OBLIGATE YOU TO ADOPT.

animal.description:
PLEASE FILL OUT AN APPLICATION FOR ADOPTION! Please do not call the shelter, until you have completed an application and are ready to make an apt for a meet and greet. Inquiries will not be answered at this time. 

Chaka and his  pack of rascally playmates were part of a hoarding situation that we helped with from another county.  These poor pups spent most of their lives locked in a rv in their own excrement.  The owner would come by once a day to feed over 20 dogs.  They have all since been spayed, neutered and had their basic needs met including, but not limited to a CLEAN living environment, vaccines and they were all treated for giardia and coccidia.  These babies are well on their way to exciting new adventures with YOU.  They are still learning how to be social and most of them are quite friendly.  We do REQUIRE for another dog to be in the house for these sweet babies at it does make them feel better!  Chaka would do great in just about any environment.  He is sweet, loving, and snuggly.  He has not shown much fear around us but he does love pets and snuggles!  Older kids may be best as they don't seem nearly as scary as small ones! Please research POSITIVE training techniques before applying to adopt. We care very much about your application answers and they are reviewed for completeness and the best match. Please fill out an application on the included link: https://threerivershs.org/adoption-app-2/ 

The adoption fee of $350 includes spay/neuter, current vaccines, microchip, free vet visit, 30 days of pet health insurance, puppy book, and engraved ID tag.

 Zane is 11 years old, housebroken, crate trained for feeding and treats. Does well if left alone. Gets along with other dogs once acclimated to the environment. Unsure about cats. Loves to snuggle and be right next to you. Gives the best kisses. He’s getting exercise and has lost some weight and showing more energy and personality. Likes to play with other dogs when he’s in the mood. Doesn’t like to be left alone outside for too long. 
He’s definitely a loud snorer ?

If you would like to meet Zane send us an email to theloveofk9s@yahoo.com and we will get back with you as quick as we can.

Adoption donation pays for all vetting...neuter, a heart worm test, all vaccinations, deworming, flea prevention, a microchip and a wellness exam

animal.description:
Trixie needs a home with:
-No kids under the age of 10. 

Meet Trixie Tang! Trixie Tang is an adorable 5-year-old Coonhound, Walker mix with a silly personality. Sweet Trixie is an active gal looking for a family to spend forever with and would love an equally active family. Trixie is still working on some basic commands and thinks it would be great if her family could help her with some positive reinforcement training! She is very treat motivated so learning new things will be a breeze for this cutie pie. Because Trixie is still working on tricks like "off" she will need a family with no children under the age of 10; she doesn't want to knock anyone over when she gets excited! Some of Trixie's favorite things include, playing with stuffy toys, eating lots of yummy treats and sniffing everything around her. She would enjoy supervised outdoor time with her family to keep her extra safe while she explores! If you are looking for a goofy and sweet doggo, then Trixie Tang is the one for you! 

If you're interested in adopting Trixie Tang, please email a completed adoption application to adoptions@kitsap-humane.org. Adoption applications and more information about our adoption process can be found on our website here: https://www.kitsap-humane.org/adopt/how-to-adopt/. Once your application has been received, you will be placed in line to have your application reviewed. All applicants are pre-screened over the phone, and then are scheduled for a time to come in and meet the dog at the shelter. animal.description:
MEET >>> Lovin Mr Doodles!!

Hi there! I'm Mr Doodles and I'm looking for a new forever home. My story is sad I got saved from the euthanisia list and went to train and board for a year, where I was so lonely, because I just love my humans! I came back to phoenix, and this nice man adopted me but he is a paraplegic and I'm just too strong for him. And while he loves me so very much, I need to find a new home. I need a home with a nice backyard to run in. I love to play fetch and love walks, but I am a strong boy! Oh so handsome loving Decker is back in town and looking for forever! This kid loves his humans so much! Decker was saved from the euthanasia list and went to board and train up north. He than got adopted by a paralegic, I am just too strong for him. (decker is 80 pounds!) While loving Mr Doodles is strong, he is a lover, total lover with people he knows. Decker loves to give kisses, and to be with his humans. I love to cuddle with my humans. I prefers to be your only animal, but has plenty of love to give. I am house trained, crate trained and love water and baths. Mr Doodles is a little grabby with food, so no kids. I am a gentle giant. I do have some skin conditions, which are improving as we speak. I will need shots about every 2 months around $100 and no grain food. I do not want to go back to boarding. I really needs a forever home asap. If you are committed and have no breed restrictions and no other animals please call 520-800-4633 leave a message if needed. Please call rather than email, as emails sometimes take a long time to get to me. My name is Mr Doodles and I would love to meet you!

If you are interested in meeting this dog, please visit our website for our online application www.underdogaz.com

PLEASE NOTE: This dog is courtesy posted for another individual or Rescue. Different policies and fees may apply.

Meet Mr. Blonde, a one and a half-year-old Chocolate Lab mix.

Mr. Blonde is a goober and a big baby weighing in at 63.5 pounds. He is just a happy boy whose mission in life is to make you smile. Mr. Blonde wants love and attention, it doesn't take much to please him. This handsome fella can't wait to find a home to call his own. He is still very puppy-ish and loves to play.

Mr. Blonde will be available for adoption on 1/29/2021 at 12:18 PM.

If you are interested in adopting this pet please fill out an adoption questionnaire at www.yakimahumane.org. A Yakima Humane Society staff member will contact you once your questionnaire has been received.

If you would like to adopt this pet you can fill out an online adoption form at www.yakimahumane.org. Please give the name and ID number for the animal you wish to adopt.
If you are thinking about adding a pet to your family, be a hero, please consider adopting a shelter pet and if you already have pets – for life’s sake – spay and neuter. Spaying and neutering your pets is the single most important thing you can do to help decrease our nations severe pet overpopulation.
*NOTE: Nearly 90% of the animals that come into our shelter are abandoned, neglected, traumatized, injured, or ill. We attempt to give our best assessment of the animal’s welfare and temperament. Unfortunately, due to lack of funding, volunteers, and resources our physical and mental assessment of the animal is not always 100% correct.

animal.description:
Meet Sissy, an approximately 8-10 years of age who became a Misfit stray found wandering in Chickasha. This pet is  , up to date on all age-appropriate vaccinations and preventatives, heart-worm negative, and micro-chipped!

She is House trained and uses an electronic doggie door.  She is treat-motivated.

She is good with cats, dogs and children.  She has a low energy level and will sit in your lap all day!  She sometimes gets jealous when food is being served when other dogs are nearby.

Sissy is a loving gentle incredibly sweet girl.  She is a medium size dog, very quiet and low key.  Even though she had 18 of her teeth surgically removed recently, she likes her wet food.  She really likes scrambled eggs on Sunday morning!  She sleeps well all night long.  She particularly likes sleeping in front of the fireplace on a nice fluffy bed.  She likes the warm sunshine and will sunbathe on the porch.  She takes an interest in family by wanting to be included in the group.  She has one dark eye and one blue eye which makes her unique!  

You can apply to meet / adopt this pet at www.muttmisfits.com/adoption-application!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Our sweet little Ice Cream puppies are ready for their new homes! This litter came to us after their mama got hit by a car :-( they needed to be kept safe! They are little chihuahua mixes, just over 3 months old.

The puppies are full of life! There is never a dull moment with 6 puppies running around! They are very playful, sometimes rough but always ready for cuddles with their foster family. They live with other dogs of various sizes in their foster home and do well with everyone. They like the house cats too! Although they have not been exposed to kids while in rescue, we do not believe there will be an issue as long as the kids are kind and respectful of their small statures. Housetraining is still a skill in need of work - right now they use pee pads. One or two will venture outside into the snow but then quickly hightail it back inside! They love toys and chewies are a favorite. They are gated or penned at night and when their foster family is gone for the day. They still need training and that

Neapolitan or Neo as his foster mom calls him has stolen everyone's heart! He is full of mischief and likes to get in trouble! A champion wrestler too! When he is all wiped out Neo likes to cuddle up with his siblings and anyone else that will have him. He will do what ever it takes to get his foster mom's attention so she picks him up. If someone wants to spoil a little dog, this may be the boy for you!

Neo is scheduled to be vetted on Feb 2 but we are accepting applications now. He will be neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, flea/worm treated at the time. His adoption fee is $400

animal.description: Meet our darling Toasty, our almost 3 year old, small pit mix. Toasty has been adopted out twice here, but just cannot seem to find the right home, even though there are a lot of different types of homes that she can fit into. Both of her previous homes note how loving, affectionate and cuddly she is in the home. She can get along with multiple people in the house as well, but would be better suited with older children. She sleeps well, is potty trained and has her basic commands down as well. She enjoys to run around the yard, chase balls, and chew on her squeaky toys, so she is also trained on appropriate methods to help get her energy out. Toasty is missing the home life and would like to show you how good of a companion she can be. If you are interested in meeting Toasty, please fill out an application at www.highsierraanimalrescue.org. We do not discuss potential adoptions without an already submitted application.

animal.description: My name is Lexa! I'm incredibly loving and cuddly. But I also love playing. I'm laid back and go with the flow for the most part, but I can run for miles if that's your jam. Sometimes I get too excited about running and barrel into your knees. I also forget that I'm bigger than the smaller humans and knock them over. But I'm the best cuddler. I love being the little spoon or just leaning against you! Also, I play dress up! If I see my sweater, I try to dive bomb it to get it on as fast as possible! I love grooming other dogs, the cats (who sometimes don't want me too and then I pout), and rabbits. The last bunny I lived with was fast! I didn't chase her though unless she initiated it and even then I stopped before I got too close. I love playing with other dogs as long as I'm given time to get to know them. I make a lot of loud noises when I play and I can be super dramatic. I would steal my sister's ball when I wanted her to run with me! l love walks but I do still pull sometimes when I get excited, but I'm easily trainable, especially if you have yummy treats. I'm kennel trained and house trained. I'm not very toy motivated, but I like treats and jumping in water. I hope I find someone who gives me lots of affection and lots of running!
animal.name: Lexa

I'd like to introduce myself - Benny is the name, Benz for short. I'm the newest member of the HBR family. I may be small, but I am mighty! I love walks, toys, people, food, naps, my new bed, toys, snuggles, and did I mention toys? I'm a 4 year old Frenchie who is trying his best to figure out how to live with an older bulldog and a very strange animal called a ""cat"" - I'm very excited to have fur siblings, but they aren't quite as excited as I am! I'm working on eating better and figuring out how to fix my skin allergies/condition - but I am positive I'll get there! I am definitely a lap dog and I try to sit in my foster mom's lap when she is working. I sleep in my crate and go to the bathroom outside like a pro! I'm almost the perfect dog. At least that's what my story is so I can find my forever folks when I am ready!

Love, Benz

animal.description:
Meet Ducky!
* We do not reply to inquiries.
* If you see this post, Ducky is still available.
* You must fill out an application in order to adopt. 

Ducky is a male 4 month old Lab/Hound/Shepherd mix who we expect to be about 60 lbs full grown. He was found alone as a stray so it takes him a little bit of time to get comfortable with new situations.

Ducky is a mellow pup that is just trying to navigate his new world. Each day he gets more and more confident and he is figuring out how to play and be the goofy pup that he is! He’s discovering the joy of toys and puppy zoomies and loves to get all the attention. 

Ducky loves his humans. He really depends on them and loves to snuggle and hangout. We are looking for a family with older kids or a couple that is looking for a new companion!

Ducky is completely crate trained and is working on his house training, which gets better everyday. He is on schedule for his vaccinations and has been deemed healthy for adoption by our local vet. Ducky is not yet neutered so this will be your responsibility as the adopter to do so when he reaches the appropriate age of 7-9 months.

If you are interested in giving this sweet boy the loving home he deserves, please fill out an application on our website, www.outriderdogs.com, under our ‘Rescue’ page.

Thank you!
Outrider Dogs Rescue

Facebook & Instagram: @outriderdogs

animal.description: Meet Lizzie! Lizzie is a very special girl and is one of our longest residents! Lizzie is a 2 year old Pit mix that always has a smile on her face! She takes a few extra seconds to warm up to new people, but once she does she is the biggest love! When she first came to us, she was petrified! She didn't seem like she had ever felt a loving hand! She has had lots of them during her time here and she can't get enough! Lizzie loves giving you hugs to show her affection. And trust us, they're the best hugs ever! We have been doing "clicker" training with her and she has responded so well! All she wants to do is please! Lizzie would do best in a quiet home without any young kids (16+), due to her sometimes getting overstimulated. She would do well with another dog, as long as its the right match. Lizzie is looking for her forever home that has nothing but love to give! If you are interested in meeting our sweetest Lizzie, please fill out a questionnaire (either in person or online at gobroomecounty.com/shelter) and staff will contact those we would like to move forward with. If you have further questions about Lizzie, please call the shelter at (607)778-2493 or email us at muttsrus@broomecounty.us.

animal.description: Meet Brute! This handsome lad was found by a good samaritan and was never claimed. He is a Shapei/Lab mix. Brute has shown to be very sweet and laid back. He recently underwent entropion corrective surgery. Entropion is when the upper and/or lower eyelids roll inward the eye causing the hair to constantly rub and irritate against the eye ball. Shapei's are the poster child for this condition. This surgery should correct this and should not cause any further health concerns in the future. Brute looks a little rough post surgery, and it will tend to look worse before it improves, but we are hoping his future home can overlook is current appearance and open their hearts and offer a forever loving family.
animal.name: Brute

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Shih Tzu/Maltese | 6-months old | 5 pounds | Adoption Fee: $575Let me introduce you to the newest member of the Rescue Crew. Matador was found in a abandoned house very skinny and full of mats and only weighed about 5 lbs when he was removed from the home. We do not know anything about his life before he came into rescue , but what we do know now is that Matador is the sweetest and most energetic puppy. He favorite pastime is playing fetch , getting belly rubs, following foster mom around the house and going for walks inside her jacket. He loves woman and is very sweet around his foster mom's 5 month old grandchild but can be very nervous and vocal around men, When a male enters the home he barks and becomes very protective of his territory . Speaking of his loud voice, he loves to alert his foster mom of every little sound he hears, so a family living in a apartment or townhouse would not be a good fit for him.

When this sweetheart arrived , he was not at all potty trained. But now with his hard work, he is now about 50% there.

Matador also is not a big fan of his crate but is learning to adjust to it more everyday. He still barks a lot when his mom leaves for work but is now learning that at the end of the day, she will come back home to him.

Matador does fine around large dogs (he currently has 4 large foster siblings) but is protective of his food around them. He has no fear of chasing them away from his bowl of food. He is learning that he will always have a bowl full of food to fill his belly. We don't think he has been socialized with other dogs in his past, but he is learning to co exist with my dogs and is getting so much better with his manners around them. Over time, he has become more comfortable with them and likes to try to be the alpha.

Please submit a application If you think you may be a good fit to give this sweet boy an amazing life that he so deserves.

The adoption fee covers the cost of the animal's spay/neuter surgery, microchipping, FIV/FeLK testing (for cats) or Heartworm Testing (for dogs), deworming and all core age appropriate vaccinations. For the most complete information regarding this animal, and all of our adoptable pets, please ensure you are visiting our website directly at www.RescueCrew.org. You can also access the necessary online adoption application here as well. Thank you.

animal.description:
Meet Britt. Born approximately October 2020, she is super cute and sweet and loves everyone she meets. She is curious, bouncy, and fun but also loves to be cuddled.

There is a lot for a Great Pyrenees/Siberian Husky mix puppy to learn, so she will need to find a home where someone is very available to her in these early days. She loves the companionship of other animals and requires another dog to act as her mentor as she continues to understand her new world's rules.

Currently, her Foster family is teaching her the difference between her toys and others' prized possessions. This cute little girl is not going to be little for long. Now is the best time to jump in and continue mentoring her. It is going to be so fun watching her fill out and fit into those big paws. Please complete an Adoption Application. Britt is only available for adoption in OR and WA.

PUPPIES ARE ONLY PLACED IN HOMES WITH YOUTHFUL, PLAYFUL RESIDENT DOGS.

Our requirements for puppy adoption are simple and necessary.

Our puppies are not livestock guardians, they are family pets that live inside the family home.

Puppies must be placed in homes with a youthful, adult resident dog of similar size. This gives the puppy a mentor and a solid foundation for becoming part of the family.

Puppies are only adopted to homes with someone at home at least part of the day. If no one is home for 6-8 hours at a time, please do not apply.

Preference is always given to those with Great Pyrenees experience.

Applicants must have secure, visible fencing and a socialization plan in place.

The fastest way to be considered for a puppy is to fill out an application. Adoption is not first come, first served. GPRS and its fosters work diligently to find the right fit for each and every unique dog and puppy.

Applicant's personal pets must be current on vaccines & heartworm/flea prevention and be altered.

Adoption Fee: $450 (Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, heartworm test, rabies, distemper, parvo and health certificate for travel). Northwest adopters pay the cost of transport to independent transport service ($225). Adoption applications can be found on our website at

https://www.greatpyreneesrescuesociety.org/

ADOPTION, FOSTERING, AND DONATIONS are just some of the ways you can help a rescued dog. We have worked hard to cultivate a large network of volunteers to save this majestic breed. While monetary donations are always much appreciated, you can also help by donating your time as a GPRS foster or volunteer!

animal.description:
Chet is a 10 yr young, 25 lb. terripoo - tan/fawn and brown. He's a young-looking 10. Very handsome lad who came from his one and only home. Death in his family and subsequent move out of state is his reason for needing another loving family. He is used to a calm, loving 9 year old female beagle. House trained. His family says he loves a routine, especially going for a walk out in the front yard every day.
He is wary of strangers and has not yet accepted B&B staff as BFFs. We are giving him CBD oil to help his fears. So it may take him some time to learn to trust as his own pace.....patience, training on your part, LTC, CBD......will all help. Complimentary training book authored by Terri Steuben with each adoption.
We're gonna see if our groomer can spiff him up and give him some Reiki treatments to help his disposition.
Email your application (see beaglesandbuddies.com - adopt a dog section) and give us at least a week thereafter to review and email you back for a one hour appt on Fridays/Saturdays 10 am to 2 pm or Sundays from 10 to noon. Carefully proofread app - we cannot process incomplete forms. Let us know how long your dog/s are home alone on any given day-now and after pandemic abates....full descriptions of any other dogs in the home - age, weight, breed, disposition and pretty much same for human kiddos. Thanx!

Are you my furrever family?

For further info on the adoption process, please visit our home page and check out the "Adopt a Dog" section, which has thorough instructions. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and

fully vaccinated before adoption; they have been wormed, bathed, socialized, walked daily and much loved; each adoptee leaves with a leash, collar, and all medical records.

Our prices are higher than the shelters' because we nurse the dogs through their illnesses and get them needed surgeries and dentals. We also spend time socializing. Furthermore, unlike shelters, rescues do not get financial aid from the government and must rely on donations, grants, and adoption fees. Our fees for adults start at $150 and go up to $750. The higher end is for our most in demand dogs, such as young beagles and other purebred dogs. The lower end is for dogs who have been here a while. For puppies, we may go beyond this and charge $1000. The good news is that, because rescues fall under the "charity" category, the fees for our dogs are officially donations and are therefore tax deductible. You can think of it as donating to a worthy cause and getting a dog in return!

Sponsor Me

Beagles & Buddies must find ways to raise money so we can continue saving dogs. Your tax-deductible donation keeps our rescue kennel operating!

Hours

Friday: 10 am to 3 pm

Saturday: 10 am to 3 pm

Sunday: 10 am to 3 pm

Monday: CLOSED

Tuesday: CLOSED

Wednesday: CLOSED

Thursday: CLOSED



Weekday appointments may be available. We are a small staff and do our best to accommodate your needs. **Note that during COVID, we are not holding open houses on any day. Please email us for an appointment and include your application (found on our website, beaglesandbuddies.com, under "Forms"). Most appointments will be Friday through Sunday, though other days may also be available. We usually schedule one appointment per hour. Allow 1-2 hours for your appointment. Please look at our website and make a list of one or more dogs that you would like to see.

Contacting Us

If you have a question about adopting, giving up a dog, boarding, or volunteering, please visit the appropriate tabs on our
home page.

For more specific questions, call 626-444-9664 (please leave a voicemail if no answer) or email at beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Note that
Emailing
is always preferred!

Thanks!

animal.description: If interested in adopting a pet from our shelter you will need to fill out a request to adopt. There will be a overnight wait to get this approved. If approved, there is a $20 adoption fee for cats, and kittens. Adult dogs adoption fee is $75.00. Adoption fees for adult dogs at the shelter more than 2 weeks reduces to $25. Adoption fee for puppies or purebred dogs (no papers) is $100.  If not spayed or neutered, a deposit is required. The deposit is $130 for dogs and $55 for cats. Your deposit is returned after the animal is spayed/neutered. All animals adopted from the shelter MUST be spayed/neutered. Dogs arriving at the shelter receive DA2PP and Bordetella. Cats receive a vaccine for Rhinotracheitis-Calici-Panleukopenia-Chlamydia Psittaci. The animals at our shelter have been picked up stray. Please remember this when requesting additional information about the animals. Questions can be emailed to emporiakansasanimalshelter@gmail.com

animal.description:
Hey! Get to know me, Shey! My birthday is coming up and it'll be great to PAWty in the comforts of my new home. I will be 6 years old in March and am a petite, pretty Pit Bull mix. I was found as a stray, but happened to be chipped. However, my first family rehomed me, and my most recent family couldn't be located. I wasn't in the best shape though, so it's probably for the best. I was skinny, dirty and needing medical care. I got that and then some here! I'm feeling so much better. I can be anxious, but I love getting affection from people. I am sweet girl, love to get belly rubs and maybe play with some toys. A home with kids over 10 years old is recommended for me. I can be unsure of some handling, and I prefer to be left alone while eating. I love food and at times can be grabby when it comes to yummy snacks. I eat out of a slow feeder here, and it might be good to continue doing so as my food is gone as fast as it arrived! I did not mind meeting a cat or a dog here. I was off leash with both and behaved appropriately. I wasn't much into playing with another dog, but we coexisted well and just enjoyed each other's company.

Medical: Shey has tested positive for Anaplasmosis during her time at HSHA.  Anaplasmosis is a tick-borne disease (similar to Lyme) caused by the infectious bacterial organism Anaplasma phagocytophilum.  Infection often causes lameness, joint pain, fever, lethargy, and anorexia (lack of appetite), or a serious condition called thrombocytopenia which causes low platelet counts and can effect blood clotting.  Shey has received treatment with 3-4 weeks of oral antibiotic to help clear the infection.  We recommend speaking with your veterinarian about the condition and following their recommendations for ongoing care and routine monitoring (which may include annual blood testing). 
 
Client Education Document:
https://vcahospitals.com/know-your-pet/anaplasmosis-in-dogs

Name: Abbot

DOB: 12/24/2014

Weight: 15.9lb

Adoption Fee: 325.00

Abbot

**Foster known as Rocky**

"IF I can change and you can change, everybody can change." - Rocky Balboa

Underneath his tough exterior, Rocky is this sweet, spunky, humorous and awesome little dude! His #1 goal is to make you feel special by letting you know you're his everything. Once you have developed a mutual trust, He will go the ends of the earth for you. He will want to know you feel the same for him. A few soft hot dogs, some floor time with toys, kind-hearted patience, a soft voice, snuggles under the covers & you will earn his undying love.

Rocky does seem to prefer the ladies over the gents. He is fine with men once you work him through his fear. It shouldn't take long, he now loves his foster dad just after a week! In transition in his foster's home , Rocky was quite vocal so shared walls (townhouse, etc) may not be the best living situation for this guy. After he became comfortable though, his voice became quieter and he is rarely heard barking.

Rocky enjoys not only his favorite human(s) but also enjoys the companionship of another dog. Another dog isn't required but it might make his transition a bit smoother and his days a bit happier! As far as cats, probably not the best match for Rocky according to his Texas foster.

Rocky prefers to roam free in the house. He resists being crated but has done fantastic in his foster's home when left out. He would love nothing more than to sleep the night away in his human's cushy bed.

Rocky is house-broken but "marks". He is learning to change this behavior by wearing belly bands and having close supervision when not wearing his belly band. Belly bands are easy to purchase off Amazon, cheap and re-useable. Rocky's definitely making improvements every day and will hopefully soon enough not need to wear these bands anymore!

Rocky is full of antics! He might pick up a shoe and throw it in up the air, trying to catch it again & again! Or, he might push his toy around like a vacuum. Whatever the case, He's sure to make you belly laugh! When not involved in playful fun, Rocky might be found snoozing in the sun, curled up in your arms, or asking for a walk! He walks great on a leash by the way! And, even though a Texas transplant, Rocky's really been having some fun outdoors in the snow!

**Rocky would not be best fitted in a home with young kids ** older respectful kids only please.

If you think you have what it takes to invest in Rocky's forever home, Consider applying to meet Rocky today!

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal.

Please check out our website,

www.ruffstartrescue.org

for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals!

All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs).

Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept.

Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies:

http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

animal.description:
Otis is scheduled to be neutered on 2/16/2021. He will available for adoption afterwards!

Meet Otis!

Otis came to AWS on 1/25/2021 from Jefferson County Animal Control. He was picked up as a stray and his family never came for him.

He’s now with AWS in the hopes of finding a new home!

Otis is believed to be a Bassett Hound/Shepherd mix and he is estimated to be around 3 years old. He weighs about 45.6 pounds.

He doesn’t seem to mind other dogs or cat, but we are unsure how he is with children. We do require meet and greets with other dogs and children. He may need some help with housebreaking after being in the shelter environment, but we believe that once he is on a schedule he will do fine!

Otis is a very outgoing, vocal boy who craves attention from people!
